Always good to remember Gene Wolfe's model where aliens have three layers. First: an external mask of a human face, badly fitting, suspicious and uncanny, worn to "blend in". Similar to how in urban legends men in black (MIBs) wear human cadavers and animate them, but are demons.

Per Junger microscopy itself deforms the thing studied, taking it out of its natural perspective, thus making in monstrous. Ants are not meant to be seen up close. But the third face is a human one. One recalls Raphael in Tobit arriving as a relative, or the Swedenborgian heresy.

Underneath there is a monstrous face of pure horror. Tentacled, manacled, twisted, deformed, an alien monster. But it turns out that one is a mask too. The alien face is simply the faces of various insects and crawling bugs we see every day on earth, magnified and worn as a mask.
